en_649015_0	President Maithripala Sirisena has said that the teacher should intervene to make the child a subject matter expert and a humanist.
en_649015_1	The President made this observation joining in a function organized to hand over graduate teacher appointments to those who has passed in the Western Provincial teacher examination.
en_649015_2	Graduate teacher appointment were handed over to 587 in the first round from among 15,000 applicants who sat the teacher competitive examination held in June 2019.
en_649015_3	The event was held at the Sri Lanka Foundation Institute.
en_649015_4	Symbolizing the teacher appointment the President handed over the letters of appointments to 10 teachers.
en_649015_5	Addressing the gathering, President Maithripala Sirisena said that the future of a child is being decided through the teacher.
en_649015_6	As such the President mentioned that decisions with respect to children should be taken with a broad awareness.
en_649015_7	Speaking further the President said thatone of the motives of the government is to create an educated society which provides equal opportunities for the people.
en_649015_8	He pointed out the need for teachers to upgrade their knowledge in par with technology to sustain themselves in the profession.
en_649015_9	The President stressed the need for teachers to help support the process of rearing educated and decent children as intellectuals to society.
en_649015_10	While mentioning that teachers play a decisive role in a studentâ€™s future, Mr. Sirisena noted that they must have a deep understanding on matters concerning children while making decisions related to them.
